preface.para:
This guide is divided into four parts organized by Conventions archctectural
layers plus one part for general utilities components provided by the framework and one more part for Conventions Scaffolding a code generation tool based on JBoss Forge. 
is represented by conventions managed beans which are wrappers to CDI beans; 
shows how the framework is integrated with CDI, Hibernate and EJB to provide database operations;  discusses the view layer and its UI helper components;
talks about the model layer and its helper classes;  walks throught utilities components such as properties provider, security helper, anotated queries, i18n, paginator and so on;
                                                                            Demostrates Conventions Scaffold, a tool based on 
                                                                           JBoss Forge to enable boilerplate code generation for 
                                                                           Conventions Framework.
